'''Myōken-gū''' (妙見宮), '''Myōkendō''' (妙見堂), or '''Myōken Shrine''' (妙見神社) are [[Shinto shrines]] located in various regions of Japan. The enshrined deities are [[Ame-no-Minakanushi]] and the [[North Star]].

* {{ill|Myōken Shrine (Tokyo)|ja|妙見神社 (東京都)|12=draft}} - Located on [[Myōken Island]].
* {{ill|Chiba Shrine|ja|千葉妙見宮|12=draft}} - Located in [[Chūō-ku, Chiba]], [[Chiba Prefecture]].
* {{ill|Hoshida Myokengu|ja|星田妙見宮|3=小松神社_(交野市)|1=Hoshida Myokengu|12=draft}} - Located in [[Katano]], [[Osaka Prefecture]].
* {{ill|Iwaya Myōken-gū|ja|岩屋妙見宮|12=draft}} - Located in [[Nio-chō]], [[Mitoyo]], [[Kagawa Prefecture]].
* {{ill|Myōken Shrine (Naruto)|ja|妙見神社 (鳴門市)|12=draft}} - Located in [[Muyachō Hayashizaki]], [[Naruto]], [[Tokushima Prefecture]].
* {{ill|Myōken-gū (Tōyō)|ja|妙見宮 (東洋町)|12=draft}} - Located in Shirahama, [[Tōyō]], [[Aki District]], [[Kōchi Prefecture]].
* {{ill|Myōken-gū (Yatsushiro)|ja|妙見宮 (八代市)|12=draft}} - Located in [[Yatsushiro]], [[Kumamoto Prefecture]].
* {{ill|Mioya Shrine (Adachiyama Myōken-gū)|ja|御祖神社|1=Adachi Myokengu|2=ja|3=御祖神社|4=fr|5=Adachi Myokengu|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Adachiyama Myokengu|1=Adachi Myokengu|4=fr|5=Adachi Myokengu|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Adachiyama Myokengu|12=draft}} - Located in [[Kokurakita-ku]], [[Kitakyushu]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture]]. Since [[1945]], also known as the General Myōken Shrine of Japan.
* Former name of {{ill|Taga Shrine (Nogata)|ja|多賀神社 (直方市)|12=draft}} in [[Nogata]].
* {{ill|Katsuragi Shrine Myōken-gū|ja|葛城神社妙見宮|12=draft}} - Located in [[Chikujō]], [[Chikujō District]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture]].

